1
00:00:05,320 --> 00:00:06,680
(Discussing coffee terminology)
Espresso Martini.

2
00:00:06,680 --> 00:00:08,110
(International-style cafe)
Espresso Martini.

3
00:00:08,110 --> 00:00:09,560
(Coming up in this episode)

4
00:00:09,560 --> 00:00:12,680
(Ning gives it a try)
Espresso Martini.

5
00:00:12,680 --> 00:00:14,160
(English reading lesson)
Delight.

6
00:00:14,160 --> 00:00:15,240
(Outside my field of expertise)
This is difficult.

7
00:00:15,240 --> 00:00:15,980
(Artistic atmosphere is off the charts)

8
00:00:18,040 --> 00:00:19,680
I wanted to learn ballet
when I was a child.

9
00:00:19,680 --> 00:00:20,440
What role did you dance?

10
00:00:20,440 --> 00:00:21,120
The ugly duckling?

11
00:00:25,240 --> 00:00:26,320
(Trying to save face)
Don't pull me. Stop pulling me.

12
00:00:26,840 --> 00:00:27,960
(I wasn't even pulling you)
Fine, I won't.

13
00:00:27,960 --> 00:00:28,900
(Still provoking him)
What's wrong?

14
00:00:29,180 --> 00:00:30,340
(Completely losing it)

15
00:00:30,400 --> 00:00:31,240
(The cafe's comedy service is now open)
How many villains are there?

16
00:00:31,240 --> 00:00:31,960
Do you know?

17
00:00:31,960 --> 00:00:33,200
Could it be you?

18
00:00:33,200 --> 00:00:34,400
(Look me in the eye)
Are you the culprit?

19
00:00:34,400 --> 00:00:36,080
(Ning denies it)
No. It wasn't me.

20
00:00:36,080 --> 00:00:38,360
Last episode, Zhou Keyu drew
the culprit role himself.

21
00:00:38,360 --> 00:00:39,200
Everyone figured it out

22
00:00:39,200 --> 00:00:40,400
except for one genius.

23
00:00:40,400 --> 00:00:41,760
Can you guess who that genius was?

24
00:00:41,780 --> 00:00:42,240
(You)

25
00:00:42,240 --> 00:00:43,440
Sun Qian has played deduction games

26
00:00:43,440 --> 00:00:44,200
before too, right?

27
00:00:44,200 --> 00:00:44,880
I'm too timid.

28
00:00:44,880 --> 00:00:45,760
(Easily frightened)
I don't dare go.

29
00:00:45,760 --> 00:00:47,440
I'm here to entertain.

30
00:00:47,440 --> 00:00:48,480
(A lighthearted script)
Something cheerful and fun.

31
00:00:48,480 --> 00:00:49,960
(Trying to mislead her)
That's exactly what our show is.

32
00:00:49,960 --> 00:00:51,280
(Seeing through the act)
We're all comedians here.

33
00:00:51,280 --> 00:00:52,400
(Comedienne)
She's our comedienne.

34
00:00:52,400 --> 00:00:53,880
(Question:)
Best foods for weight loss?

35
00:00:53,880 --> 00:00:54,880
It has to be a pun.

36
00:00:54,880 --> 00:00:56,240
(Praise me)
A pretzel?

37
00:00:56,300 --> 00:00:56,780
(Chicken breast)

38
00:00:56,940 --> 00:00:57,660
(Eating for free)

39
00:00:59,640 --> 00:01:01,040
(Saving the cafe's electricity bill)
We don't even need air conditioning.

40
00:01:03,100 --> 00:01:06,140
=Truth Clubhouse=

41
00:01:06,260 --> 00:01:09,140
(First day at Starlight Cafe)

42
00:01:10,000 --> 00:01:12,020
(Jin Cardashian)
Why have you been

43
00:01:12,020 --> 00:01:14,920
(Observe)
so distant with me today?

44
00:01:14,920 --> 00:01:16,680
(Please go easy on me)
Can you not suspect me today?

45
00:01:16,680 --> 00:01:19,620
I got eliminated
because of you last round.

46
00:01:19,620 --> 00:01:20,620
I can't believe you chose me.

47
00:01:20,660 --> 00:01:22,380
(Utterly baffled)
That was such a terrible choice.

48
00:01:22,390 --> 00:01:22,900
What do I do now?

49
00:01:22,900 --> 00:01:25,100
(Requesting a retake)
Can we film that again?

50
00:01:25,100 --> 00:01:26,940
I want everyone back
in the same styling.

51
00:01:26,940 --> 00:01:28,660
Or maybe I should just film
my own version.

52
00:01:30,880 --> 00:01:31,520
Zhang Linghe.

53
00:01:31,520 --> 00:01:32,360
Hello.

54
00:01:34,040 --> 00:01:35,640
(Qian Jinding's first appearance)
Qian, come over here.

55
00:01:36,620 --> 00:01:37,700
(A little flustered)

56
00:01:38,400 --> 00:01:39,680
Are you that nervous?

57
00:01:39,680 --> 00:01:41,040
You nearly dropped it.

58
00:01:41,040 --> 00:01:42,280
How did it fall apart

59
00:01:42,280 --> 00:01:43,240
so quickly?

60
00:01:43,760 --> 00:01:44,720
(Completely confused)
What fell apart?

61
00:01:44,720 --> 00:01:45,880
(Polite mode activated)
You sit down.

62
00:01:45,880 --> 00:01:46,280
No, you sit.

63
00:01:46,280 --> 00:01:46,580
No,

64
00:01:46,580 --> 00:01:46,920
it's fine.

65
00:01:46,920 --> 00:01:47,520
No.

66
00:01:47,520 --> 00:01:48,760
Let's sit together.

67
00:01:48,760 --> 00:01:49,720
Jin, sit here.

68
00:01:49,720 --> 00:01:50,720
(Please don't leave)
No.

69
00:01:50,720 --> 00:01:51,400
No.

70
00:01:51,400 --> 00:01:52,240
She's scared.

71
00:01:52,840 --> 00:01:54,320
(Making introductions)
This is Ning.

72
00:01:54,320 --> 00:01:55,480
Hello.

73
00:01:55,480 --> 00:01:56,440
(Well-behaved)
Hello, Ning.

74
00:01:56,720 --> 00:01:57,880
And this is Zhang Linghe.

75
00:01:57,880 --> 00:01:58,320
Hello.

76
00:01:58,380 --> 00:01:59,020
(Greetings)

77
00:01:59,120 --> 00:02:00,320
As for Ning,

78
00:02:00,320 --> 00:02:01,480
(Brutally honest review)
he's not very brave either.

79
00:02:01,480 --> 00:02:02,400
But we've trained him well.

80
00:02:02,400 --> 00:02:02,920
Really?

81
00:02:02,920 --> 00:02:04,760
Because we have people
who are even more scared.

82
00:02:04,760 --> 00:02:05,960
Me.

83
00:02:05,960 --> 00:02:07,800
(And me)
Ding and I.

84
00:02:08,280 --> 00:02:09,030
(I've figured it out)
What's that?

85
00:02:09,030 --> 00:02:09,560
A hair net.

86
00:02:09,620 --> 00:02:12,140
(Amused by the teasing)

87
00:02:12,880 --> 00:02:14,880
You haven't met before, right?

88
00:02:14,880 --> 00:02:16,200
No. I've never met Sun Qian before.

89
00:02:16,920 --> 00:02:18,080
You haven't met Zhang Linghe either?

90
00:02:18,640 --> 00:02:19,160
Me?

91
00:02:19,800 --> 00:02:20,160
I have.

92
00:02:20,160 --> 00:02:20,800
Of course I have.

93
00:02:21,920 --> 00:02:23,200
(We've worked together before)
We filmed a show together.

94
00:02:23,200 --> 00:02:24,080
That's right.

95
00:02:24,080 --> 00:02:25,200
Youth Periplous.

96
00:02:26,640 --> 00:02:28,280
You went to a murder
mystery game by yourself?

97
00:02:28,280 --> 00:02:28,920
How was it?

98
00:02:28,920 --> 00:02:30,640
It was boring.

99
00:02:30,640 --> 00:02:31,640
Is there anything

100
00:02:31,640 --> 00:02:33,000
we should know about you?

101
00:02:33,000 --> 00:02:34,040
(Supportive Ning appears)
For example, are you easily frightened?

102
00:02:34,040 --> 00:02:35,080
Very.

103
00:02:35,080 --> 00:02:35,560
Really?

104
00:02:35,560 --> 00:02:38,520
I've never even gone
into a haunted house.

105
00:02:38,520 --> 00:02:39,920
I start crying while waiting in line.

106
00:02:40,440 --> 00:02:41,240
Perfect.

107
00:02:41,460 --> 00:02:42,700
(What does that mean?)

108
00:02:42,720 --> 00:02:44,560
Wang Yuwen came last episode.

109
00:02:44,560 --> 00:02:45,320
She cried twice.

110
00:02:45,320 --> 00:02:45,940
(It was genuinely terrifying)

111
00:02:46,120 --> 00:02:47,680
Yes.

112
00:02:47,680 --> 00:02:49,080
She hid in a corner and cried quietly.

113
00:02:49,380 --> 00:02:50,940
(Shaking with fear)

114
00:02:50,960 --> 00:02:51,800
But I was surprised

115
00:02:51,800 --> 00:02:53,720
to see tears streaming down her face.

116
00:02:53,720 --> 00:02:55,080
(Starting to panic)
They just came pouring out.

117
00:02:55,080 --> 00:02:55,600
I'm scared.

118
00:02:55,600 --> 00:02:57,520
I was worried, so I didn't
wear false eyelashes.

119
00:02:57,520 --> 00:02:59,400
(Came fully prepared)
I'd be embarrassed if I cried them off.

120
00:02:59,400 --> 00:03:00,360
(Don't worry)
It's not that scary anymore.

121
00:03:00,360 --> 00:03:00,680
Really.

122
00:03:00,680 --> 00:03:02,400
Just don't pull off my wig
if you get scared.

123
00:03:02,400 --> 00:03:04,120
(Everything important is underneath)
I'm completely bald under there.

124
00:03:04,120 --> 00:03:05,920
(Little troublemaker)
Then I'll help you take it off.

125
00:03:05,920 --> 00:03:07,520
We're staying in this venue today,

126
00:03:07,520 --> 00:03:08,040
right?

127
00:03:08,040 --> 00:03:08,440
More or less.

128
00:03:08,440 --> 00:03:09,280
That's good.

129
00:03:09,280 --> 00:03:09,880
It isn't too large.

130
00:03:10,440 --> 00:03:11,760
What kind of script do you usually play?

131
00:03:11,760 --> 00:03:12,440
Comedy scripts.

132
00:03:13,400 --> 00:03:14,120
You play comedy scripts?

133
00:03:14,120 --> 00:03:16,440
You should be playing
hardcore mystery ones.

134
00:03:16,440 --> 00:03:17,720
That's what we do here.

135
00:03:17,720 --> 00:03:19,000
What level do you

136
00:03:19,000 --> 00:03:20,600
think our show is?

137
00:03:21,320 --> 00:03:23,440
(A serious misjudgment)
I thought I was here to entertain people.

138
00:03:23,440 --> 00:03:24,240
That's my department.

139
00:03:24,240 --> 00:03:26,000
I mainly handle the comedy side too.

140
00:03:26,020 --> 00:03:27,160
(A fellow competitor)

141
00:03:27,160 --> 00:03:28,880
Stealing my lane?

142
00:03:28,880 --> 00:03:30,320
I'm taking all types of jobs now.

143
00:03:31,960 --> 00:03:33,440
(Identity: Distinguished Detective)
I'm known for deduction.

144
00:03:34,220 --> 00:03:35,500
(Highly skeptical)

145
00:03:36,600 --> 00:03:37,960
(An honest confession)
I just happen to fail quite often.

146
00:03:37,960 --> 00:03:39,840
I've crashed and burned
in the last two episodes.

147
00:03:40,420 --> 00:03:41,980
(Exactly as expected)

148
00:03:42,480 --> 00:03:43,600
(Energetic Ding reporting for duty)
You're here?

149
00:03:43,600 --> 00:03:45,080
Hello.

150
00:03:45,080 --> 00:03:45,840
Why are you wearing it?

151
00:03:45,840 --> 00:03:46,280
(Apron on)

152
00:03:46,280 --> 00:03:47,240
Aren't we supposed to?

153
00:03:47,240 --> 00:03:47,880
We'll put them

154
00:03:47,880 --> 00:03:48,560
on right away.

155
00:03:49,120 --> 00:03:50,480
(Praise from the Gold Card member)
Ding is still the most obedient.

156
00:03:50,880 --> 00:03:51,760
When did you arrive yesterday?

157
00:03:52,280 --> 00:03:53,280
One o'clock.

158
00:03:53,280 --> 00:03:54,200
One in the morning?

159
00:03:54,200 --> 00:03:55,200
Morning.

160
00:03:55,200 --> 00:03:56,320
One in the afternoon?

161
00:03:56,320 --> 00:03:57,240
That startled me.

162
00:03:57,240 --> 00:03:58,000
One in the morning?

163
00:03:58,000 --> 00:03:59,040
That's something you'd do.

164
00:03:59,040 --> 00:04:00,440
You came straight from Hengdian, right?

165
00:04:00,440 --> 00:04:01,320
That's right.

166
00:04:01,320 --> 00:04:03,040
Why didn't you fly?

167
00:04:03,040 --> 00:04:04,680
(I wish I could have)
The flight was canceled.

168
00:04:04,680 --> 00:04:06,240
Because of the rain.

169
00:04:06,240 --> 00:04:07,440
We're taking the group poster photo.

170
00:04:07,440 --> 00:04:08,280
Poster? Alright.

171
00:04:08,760 --> 00:04:09,160
Come.

172
00:04:09,160 --> 00:04:09,940
(Switching into work mode)

173
00:04:10,280 --> 00:04:10,880
Perfect.

174
00:04:10,880 --> 00:04:12,600
I'm finally the same height as you.

175
00:04:12,600 --> 00:04:13,480
Great.

176
00:04:13,480 --> 00:04:15,040
How high are those heels?

177
00:04:15,960 --> 00:04:17,480
I had to go all out.

178
00:04:18,200 --> 00:04:19,760
They haven't even stood up yet.

179
00:04:20,680 --> 00:04:21,560
How does it look?

180
00:04:22,200 --> 00:04:23,120
(Striking a pose first)
I was completely convinced yesterday

181
00:04:23,120 --> 00:04:24,680
that you were the culprit.

182
00:04:24,680 --> 00:04:26,120
But the moment I received the script,

183
00:04:26,120 --> 00:04:27,240
(Proudly)
I became confused again.

184
00:04:27,600 --> 00:04:28,920
(The esteemed detective)
You've finally

185
00:04:28,960 --> 00:04:30,600
become the detective.

186
00:04:31,840 --> 00:04:33,120
Is this your first time?

187
00:04:33,120 --> 00:04:33,720
Of course.

188
00:04:33,720 --> 00:04:35,440
(A brand-new experience)
It feels like you've been here forever.

189
00:04:35,440 --> 00:04:37,120
Culprit, innocent player, detective.

190
00:04:37,120 --> 00:04:39,120
(Every role unlocked)
I've done them all.

191
00:04:39,120 --> 00:04:40,400
I'll be following your lead today.

192
00:04:40,400 --> 00:04:40,740
(Please carry me)

193
00:04:41,040 --> 00:04:42,600
Jin Jing, where did you come from?

194
00:04:42,600 --> 00:04:43,400
I came

195
00:04:43,400 --> 00:04:44,300
(Breaking into song)
from the heavens above.

196
00:04:44,300 --> 00:04:45,600
(Immediately joins in)
The heavens above.

197
00:04:47,520 --> 00:04:48,720
Beijing.

198
00:04:48,720 --> 00:04:49,840
I thought you were going to say,

199
00:04:49,840 --> 00:04:51,120
"from your heart".

200
00:04:51,420 --> 00:04:52,780
(He knows me too well)

201
00:04:54,200 --> 00:04:55,280
Where should I tie this?

202
00:04:55,280 --> 00:04:56,780
(Putting on the apron)

203
00:04:56,880 --> 00:04:57,600
What about yours?

204
00:04:57,600 --> 00:04:58,120
(No apron required)
You don't need one.

205
00:04:58,120 --> 00:04:59,400
That's right.

206
00:04:59,400 --> 00:05:01,080
(Our distinguished Gold Card member)
I'm a VIP.

207
00:05:03,360 --> 00:05:05,360
Who is the culprit today?

208
00:05:05,360 --> 00:05:06,280
Honestly...

209
00:05:06,280 --> 00:05:07,120
Could it be you?

210
00:05:07,560 --> 00:05:08,600
(Look me in the eye)
Are you the culprit?

211
00:05:08,600 --> 00:05:09,280
(Ning refuses to admit it)
No.

212
00:05:09,280 --> 00:05:09,840
It wasn't me.

213
00:05:10,400 --> 00:05:11,160
It wasn't me.

214
00:05:11,160 --> 00:05:11,840
Really, it wasn't.

215
00:05:11,840 --> 00:05:13,200
Such a strong reaction?

216
00:05:13,720 --> 00:05:14,160
Exactly.

217
00:05:14,160 --> 00:05:15,040
(A gut feeling)
That makes it even more suspicious.

218
00:05:15,040 --> 00:05:15,720
We've found one.

219
00:05:16,120 --> 00:05:17,080
How many villains are there?

220
00:05:17,080 --> 00:05:17,680
Do you know?

221
00:05:17,680 --> 00:05:18,840
There are at least

222
00:05:18,840 --> 00:05:20,920
(Speaking nonsense with a straight face)
eight villains today.

223
00:05:20,920 --> 00:05:21,640
I'm over here.

224
00:05:21,940 --> 00:05:23,640
(He is in position)
He Yiwei.

225
00:05:23,640 --> 00:05:24,560
He Yiwei.

226
00:05:24,560 --> 00:05:25,360
You're the detective,

227
00:05:25,360 --> 00:05:27,040
so things are easier for you, right?

228
00:05:27,040 --> 00:05:27,920
(Happy)
I'm the detective.

229
00:05:29,240 --> 00:05:30,400
Being the detective is quite difficult.

230
00:05:30,400 --> 00:05:34,640
From its perspective, you're
choosing between four suspects.

231
00:05:34,640 --> 00:05:35,320
For example,

232
00:05:35,320 --> 00:05:36,240
last time I was choosing

233
00:05:36,240 --> 00:05:37,360
between three people.

234
00:05:37,360 --> 00:05:37,880
Then two.

235
00:05:38,640 --> 00:05:38,920
Right.

236
00:05:38,920 --> 00:05:39,720
Sometimes you choose

237
00:05:39,720 --> 00:05:40,700
between two, or pick from a pair.

238
00:05:40,700 --> 00:05:41,760
So I can't afford

239
00:05:41,760 --> 00:05:43,200
to trust any of you easily.

240
00:05:43,200 --> 00:05:44,160
There's one person missing.

241
00:05:45,280 --> 00:05:46,640
It feels like someone isn't here.

242
00:05:46,640 --> 00:05:47,100
(It's me)

243
00:05:47,200 --> 00:05:48,910
(I think I've figured something out)
The culprit has gone to do something.

244
00:05:48,960 --> 00:05:50,880
Are you two teaming up today?

245
00:05:51,200 --> 00:05:52,440
(Matching hair color)
The two blondes.

246
00:05:52,560 --> 00:05:54,000
That was Ke's arrangement.

247
00:05:54,000 --> 00:05:54,960
(Jin's statement)
Nothing to do with me.

248
00:05:55,220 --> 00:05:56,460
(I see)

249
00:05:56,560 --> 00:05:58,160
He really has been paying
attention to me.

250
00:06:00,080 --> 00:06:02,320
Last episode, Zhou Keyu drew
the role of the culprit himself.

251
00:06:02,320 --> 00:06:03,240
Everyone saw through it

252
00:06:03,240 --> 00:06:04,400
except for one genius.

253
00:06:04,400 --> 00:06:05,720
Can you guess who that was?

254
00:06:05,940 --> 00:06:06,460
(You)

255
00:06:07,760 --> 00:06:09,000
Sun Qian is actually quite sharp.

256
00:06:09,000 --> 00:06:10,520
I need to be more careful
with you this round.

257
00:06:10,540 --> 00:06:11,600
(Now I'm being targeted)

258
00:06:11,600 --> 00:06:13,000
Sun Qian has played
this kind of deduction

259
00:06:13,000 --> 00:06:13,760
game before?

260
00:06:13,760 --> 00:06:14,400
No.

261
00:06:14,400 --> 00:06:15,840
Have you tried escape rooms?

262
00:06:15,840 --> 00:06:16,560
(Beginner)
No.

263
00:06:16,560 --> 00:06:17,440
I've never done it either.

264
00:06:17,440 --> 00:06:18,640
I'm just too timid.

265
00:06:18,640 --> 00:06:19,400
I don't dare to go.

266
00:06:19,400 --> 00:06:20,960
What about murder mystery games?

267
00:06:20,960 --> 00:06:22,400
I only tried one

268
00:06:22,400 --> 00:06:24,480
because of this show.

269
00:06:24,480 --> 00:06:26,440
But I played a casual,
lighthearted version.

270
00:06:27,000 --> 00:06:28,120
We're playing casual ones too.

271
00:06:28,120 --> 00:06:28,600
Really?

272
00:06:28,600 --> 00:06:29,280
Yes.

273
00:06:30,140 --> 00:06:31,460
(Matching mischievous smiles)

274
00:06:31,560 --> 00:06:32,520
I knew it.

275
00:06:32,520 --> 00:06:33,840
They invited me here for something

276
00:06:33,840 --> 00:06:34,720
humorous and relaxed.

277
00:06:35,340 --> 00:06:36,940
(Seeing through it but not saying it)

278
00:06:37,000 --> 00:06:37,640
This is a very

279
00:06:37,640 --> 00:06:38,800
(Just messing around)
humorous show.

280
00:06:39,440 --> 00:06:40,680
Very humorous indeed.

281
00:06:40,680 --> 00:06:42,080
We're all the comedic type.

282
00:06:42,080 --> 00:06:43,520
(Comedienne)
She's our comedienne.

283
00:06:43,520 --> 00:06:44,520
That's perfect.

284
00:06:44,520 --> 00:06:45,960
(The perfect duo)

285
00:06:45,960 --> 00:06:47,280
Last episode was way too entertaining.

286
00:06:47,740 --> 00:06:49,660
(Keyu arrives)

287
00:06:54,440 --> 00:06:55,320
But he told me

288
00:06:55,320 --> 00:06:56,680
not to wear heels.

289
00:06:56,680 --> 00:06:57,680
He said a lot of running around.

290
00:06:57,680 --> 00:06:59,650
(Friends teasing each other)
I asked if Jin Jing put him up to it.

291
00:06:59,760 --> 00:06:59,920
No.

292
00:06:59,920 --> 00:07:00,520
It'll be involved.

293
00:07:01,320 --> 00:07:03,320
(Love-hate friendship)
Then what about Jin Jing's shoes?

294
00:07:03,320 --> 00:07:04,440
I'll just jump on their backs

295
00:07:04,440 --> 00:07:05,320
and make them carry me.

296
00:07:05,320 --> 00:07:06,560
That's a bit excessive, isn't it?

297
00:07:06,560 --> 00:07:07,080
I've no choice.

298
00:07:08,120 --> 00:07:10,000
I feel a lot of pressure
when I'm around all of you.

299
00:07:10,000 --> 00:07:10,760
Zhang Linghe.

300
00:07:11,580 --> 00:07:13,340
(As expected of you)

301
00:07:13,760 --> 00:07:15,240
What am I?

302
00:07:15,240 --> 00:07:16,820
(Highest quality award)

303
00:07:16,920 --> 00:07:17,880
I'm number one in quality.

304
00:07:18,680 --> 00:07:19,520
You're number one in price.

305
00:07:19,520 --> 00:07:20,240
You're overpriced.

306
00:07:20,880 --> 00:07:21,800
Yes, I'm...

307
00:07:23,200 --> 00:07:23,800
(Sales champion)
the sales champion.

308
00:07:23,800 --> 00:07:26,160
Move a little closer.

309
00:07:26,160 --> 00:07:26,880
Perfect.

310
00:07:27,520 --> 00:07:29,320
To let you...

311
00:07:30,320 --> 00:07:31,380
(Suddenly in a high-pitched voice)
hold hands.

312
00:07:32,640 --> 00:07:33,520
What was that?

313
00:07:34,020 --> 00:07:36,900
(Getting changed)

314
00:07:41,560 --> 00:07:43,080
(Ning's lesson)
A proper waiter carries it like this.

315
00:07:43,080 --> 00:07:44,000
Why?

316
00:07:44,000 --> 00:07:44,520
Like this.

317
00:07:44,520 --> 00:07:45,080
One hand.

318
00:07:45,560 --> 00:07:46,320
Professional way.

319
00:07:46,320 --> 00:07:48,760
Holding it with both hands
looks like you're serving tea.

320
00:07:48,760 --> 00:07:49,120
Wait.

321
00:07:49,120 --> 00:07:50,080
(Proceeding cautiously)
What if I drop it?

322
00:07:50,880 --> 00:07:52,030
(Demonstrating)
The way you're holding it...

323
00:07:52,280 --> 00:07:53,000
No, I'm not.

324
00:07:53,600 --> 00:07:54,840
(And you criticize others?)
You were just correcting someone else.

325
00:07:55,520 --> 00:07:56,400
Then how should I hold it?

326
00:07:56,400 --> 00:07:56,880
Like this.

327
00:07:58,060 --> 00:07:59,300
(Trying not to laugh)

328
00:07:59,540 --> 00:08:01,020
(Too amusing)

329
00:08:01,320 --> 00:08:02,120
You're hilarious.

330
00:08:02,120 --> 00:08:02,880
You just said holding it

331
00:08:02,880 --> 00:08:04,200
that way makes you look nervous.

332
00:08:04,200 --> 00:08:05,400
Then you did the exact same thing.

333
00:08:05,400 --> 00:08:06,280
You're not doing anything?

334
00:08:07,040 --> 00:08:07,920
(I'm a VIP)
Of course not.

335
00:08:07,920 --> 00:08:08,960
(Speaking the truth)
You're here to be served, aren't you?

336
00:08:09,920 --> 00:08:10,360
Customer's here.

337
00:08:10,360 --> 00:08:11,400
Jin Cardashian.

338
00:08:11,400 --> 00:08:12,920
I can take out my Gold Card.

339
00:08:13,400 --> 00:08:14,540
(You actually have one?)
You really do have one?

340
00:08:15,840 --> 00:08:16,840
(Rich enough to be envied)
So many.

341
00:08:16,840 --> 00:08:18,920
(Serious mode)
Just give me a smile, everyone.

342
00:08:18,920 --> 00:08:19,720
Perfect.

343
00:08:19,720 --> 00:08:20,520
(Completely serious)

344
00:08:20,520 --> 00:08:20,920
Let's go.

345
00:08:21,400 --> 00:08:23,560
Ning, let's put the bracelet

346
00:08:23,560 --> 00:08:24,080
away first.

347
00:08:24,080 --> 00:08:24,840
Alright.

348
00:08:27,960 --> 00:08:29,480
The bracelet?

349
00:08:29,480 --> 00:08:30,840
You're supposed to be serving customers.

350
00:08:30,840 --> 00:08:31,580
(Working hours)

351
00:08:31,760 --> 00:08:33,220
(Burden of a sales champion)
Work pressure is immense.

352
00:08:34,980 --> 00:08:35,900
(Feeling slightly embarrassed)

353
00:08:35,910 --> 00:08:37,030
Everyone, smile.

354
00:08:37,840 --> 00:08:38,720
Three.

355
00:08:38,720 --> 00:08:39,400
Two.

356
00:08:39,400 --> 00:08:39,840
One.

357
00:08:40,100 --> 00:08:42,300
(Starlight Cafe is officially open!)

358
00:08:42,340 --> 00:08:45,300
(A cafe full of comedians)

359
00:08:45,300 --> 00:08:47,180
(Sharing snacks)
Jin Jing, would you like some candy?

360
00:08:47,180 --> 00:08:48,180
What kind?

361
00:08:48,180 --> 00:08:49,300
Maybe later.

362
00:08:49,300 --> 00:08:50,100
Really?

363
00:08:50,100 --> 00:08:51,940
I had a huge breakfast.

364
00:08:51,940 --> 00:08:53,540
And we're constantly eating
on this show anyway.

365
00:08:53,540 --> 00:08:55,340
(Everything you could want is here)
There's always food around.

366
00:08:55,340 --> 00:08:56,220
Then I'll pass.

367
00:08:56,220 --> 00:08:57,100
There's plenty to eat.

368
00:08:57,100 --> 00:08:58,500
Bread, beef jerky.

369
00:08:58,920 --> 00:09:00,840
Espresso Martini.

370
00:09:02,480 --> 00:09:03,520
Yours...

371
00:09:03,520 --> 00:09:04,560
Why is there English on it?

372
00:09:04,560 --> 00:09:06,160
(Ning has an idea)
It'd be funnier if you said it

373
00:09:06,160 --> 00:09:06,640
in Chinese.

374
00:09:06,640 --> 00:09:08,320
(Discussing coffee terminology)
Espresso Martini.

375
00:09:08,320 --> 00:09:09,600
(Correcting his own pronunciation)
Espresso Martini.

376
00:09:11,360 --> 00:09:12,600
Espresso Martini.

377
00:09:12,600 --> 00:09:15,000
Let the good vibes ignite.

378
00:09:15,000 --> 00:09:15,520
Ignite?

379
00:09:15,520 --> 00:09:16,400
(Chengxin has a question)
What does that mean?

380
00:09:16,400 --> 00:09:17,280
To spark.

381
00:09:17,280 --> 00:09:17,920
To ignite.

382
00:09:19,240 --> 00:09:19,920
It's all in English.

383
00:09:21,040 --> 00:09:22,560
And it's quite a long sentence too.

384
00:09:22,560 --> 00:09:23,240
Let me take a look.

385
00:09:23,240 --> 00:09:24,060
(Sneaking a glance)

386
00:09:24,400 --> 00:09:25,600
(Ning gives it a try)
Espresso Martini.

387
00:09:25,600 --> 00:09:28,840
Espresso Martini.

388
00:09:29,860 --> 00:09:31,360
(English reading lesson)
Delight.

389
00:09:31,360 --> 00:09:35,520
Let the good vibes ignite.

390
00:09:36,040 --> 00:09:37,160
That's difficult.

391
00:09:37,160 --> 00:09:38,360
(Outside my field of expertise)

392
00:09:38,360 --> 00:09:40,000
Some of these words are quite uncommon.

393
00:09:41,100 --> 00:09:42,540
(Jin Cardashian returns)

394
00:09:42,640 --> 00:09:44,040
I want to say something
to you in English.

395
00:09:44,040 --> 00:09:45,640
Come on, teach me how to say it.

396
00:09:45,640 --> 00:09:46,640
How do I pronounce it?

397
00:09:46,640 --> 00:09:49,520
Your Espresso Martini.

398
00:09:49,520 --> 00:09:51,120
Espresso Martini.

399
00:09:52,120 --> 00:09:55,400
Cheers to your delight.

400
00:09:55,400 --> 00:09:56,300
(Perfect pronunciation)

401
00:09:56,720 --> 00:09:59,760
Let the good vibes ignite.

402
00:09:59,760 --> 00:10:00,640
What?

403
00:10:00,640 --> 00:10:02,080
Ignite.

404
00:10:02,080 --> 00:10:02,720
What does it mean?

405
00:10:02,720 --> 00:10:04,480
(Effortlessly using it in a sentence)
Ignite your heart.

406
00:10:04,480 --> 00:10:06,160
(Requesting an easier version)
Can we stick to basic English, please?

407
00:10:06,600 --> 00:10:08,480
Had the two of you met before?

408
00:10:08,480 --> 00:10:09,320
You mean Zhou Keyu?

409
00:10:09,320 --> 00:10:10,120
No.

410
00:10:10,840 --> 00:10:13,120
(Meeting a new friend)
I've only met him and you before.

411
00:10:13,120 --> 00:10:13,960
I've met Ding as well.

412
00:10:14,320 --> 00:10:15,280
Can we drink this?

413
00:10:15,880 --> 00:10:16,520
That one is fine.

414
00:10:16,520 --> 00:10:17,720
I wouldn't recommend the other one.

415
00:10:17,720 --> 00:10:18,120
It's okay.

416
00:10:18,120 --> 00:10:19,560
(The mischievous Ning)
I'll make Jin Jing drink it.

417
00:10:19,560 --> 00:10:21,000
(Playful Zhou)
If its served, you have to drink it.

418
00:10:21,340 --> 00:10:22,700
(The cheerful customer)

419
00:10:22,880 --> 00:10:24,480
Which one is my pudding coffee?

420
00:10:24,480 --> 00:10:25,800
The pudding has sunk to the bottom.

421
00:10:26,080 --> 00:10:27,080
(The pudding has disappeared)
The pudding.

422
00:10:28,080 --> 00:10:30,480
(Scooping up the pudding by hand)
Just fish it out and show her.

423
00:10:30,760 --> 00:10:31,840
Or finish the drink yourself.

424
00:10:31,840 --> 00:10:33,000
See? The pudding is right here.

425
00:10:33,000 --> 00:10:33,500
(Love you)

426
00:10:34,080 --> 00:10:35,040
You're the culprit.

427
00:10:35,040 --> 00:10:36,120
I'm the detective.

428
00:10:36,960 --> 00:10:37,600
I'm the culprit?

429
00:10:37,600 --> 00:10:38,480
(Teasing Ding)
How do you know you're the detective?

430
00:10:39,680 --> 00:10:40,480
Didn't you read the script?

431
00:10:40,480 --> 00:10:41,520
I'll have you executed.

432
00:10:41,520 --> 00:10:42,480
Little culprit.

433
00:10:43,080 --> 00:10:44,920
What gives you the right
to interrogate us?

434
00:10:44,920 --> 00:10:46,080
Who do you think the culprit is?

435
00:10:46,080 --> 00:10:46,600
(The detective takes charge)

436
00:10:46,600 --> 00:10:47,760
What gives you the right?

437
00:10:47,760 --> 00:10:48,360
I don't have any.

438
00:10:48,360 --> 00:10:49,420
(Bold move)

439
00:10:49,900 --> 00:10:50,340
(Say that again)

440
00:10:50,340 --> 00:10:50,940
(Wrong person to challenge)

441
00:10:51,160 --> 00:10:52,880
(Learning his place)
Sir.

442
00:10:52,880 --> 00:10:53,880
(Final warning)
Say that again.

443
00:10:54,460 --> 00:10:55,460
(I spoke out of turn)

444
00:10:56,960 --> 00:10:58,200
The five of us really do look like

445
00:10:58,200 --> 00:10:59,280
staff waiting to take orders.

446
00:10:59,280 --> 00:11:00,240
(Would you like to sign up
for a membership card?)

447
00:11:00,240 --> 00:11:00,880
We'll stand in a row.

448
00:11:08,760 --> 00:11:10,600
Let's pretend to be busy
at the beginning.

449
00:11:10,600 --> 00:11:11,240
No problem.

450
00:11:11,660 --> 00:11:12,580
(Straight into character)

451
00:11:13,220 --> 00:11:20,900
(Experts at looking busy)

452
00:11:20,920 --> 00:11:22,200
We'll wait for Jin's cue.

453
00:11:26,740 --> 00:11:29,020
(Working and singing at the same time)

454
00:11:29,400 --> 00:11:31,600
Alright.

455
00:11:31,600 --> 00:11:33,320
That smells pretty good.

456
00:11:33,320 --> 00:11:34,440
Doesn't it?

457
00:11:36,040 --> 00:11:37,000
You can really eat it raw?

458
00:11:37,720 --> 00:11:38,680
It's surprisingly good raw.

459
00:11:40,400 --> 00:11:41,280
(Now I'm interested)
Not bad.

460
00:11:42,500 --> 00:11:43,180
(Come over here)

461
00:11:44,880 --> 00:11:46,880
But Ding, aren't you
the chief investigator?

462
00:11:46,880 --> 00:11:48,480
I'm the detective.

463
00:11:48,480 --> 00:11:49,880
The chief investigator?

464
00:11:49,880 --> 00:11:51,360
(Everyone, remember: I'm the detective.)
The chief investigator.

465
00:11:51,360 --> 00:11:52,120
He's the commander.

466
00:11:52,120 --> 00:11:52,580
(Commander)

467
00:11:52,880 --> 00:11:56,120
(A sincere question from a beginner)
Why is the detective making coffee?

468
00:11:56,120 --> 00:11:57,600
The detective also...

469
00:11:57,600 --> 00:11:59,260
(Even detectives have to work)
Has a service-oriented personality.

470
00:12:00,840 --> 00:12:03,120
Two people doing the same job.

471
00:12:03,120 --> 00:12:03,880
Let's stay busy.

472
00:12:04,980 --> 00:12:05,820
(Starlight Cafe, Scene 1, Take 1)

473
00:12:05,840 --> 00:12:06,960
Stand by.

474
00:12:06,960 --> 00:12:07,520
Three.

475
00:12:07,520 --> 00:12:08,000
Two.

476
00:12:08,000 --> 00:12:08,320
One.

477
00:12:15,500 --> 00:12:17,580
(Starlight Cafe)

478
00:12:19,560 --> 00:12:21,720
(Making a dazzling entrance)
Alright.

479
00:12:21,720 --> 00:12:23,440
(My moment to shine)
You can all stop pretending now.

480
00:12:23,460 --> 00:12:25,420
(Here we go again)

481
00:12:25,880 --> 00:12:27,000
Our distinguished guest.

482
00:12:27,000 --> 00:12:28,480
I haven't even finished my line yet.

483
00:12:28,480 --> 00:12:29,680
(Busy showing off)
Don't interrupt.

484
00:12:29,680 --> 00:12:31,200
Of course. Please continue.

485
00:12:32,000 --> 00:12:32,400
Ms. Jin,

486
00:12:32,400 --> 00:12:33,380
(Interrupting the performance)
let's do that again.

487
00:12:34,220 --> 00:12:35,900
(Everyone bursts into laughter)

488
00:12:37,420 --> 00:12:38,580
(I'll be back)

489
00:12:38,760 --> 00:12:39,920
Don't talk over her lines.

490
00:12:39,920 --> 00:12:40,760
Alright.

491
00:12:40,760 --> 00:12:42,640
This is difficult to turn.

492
00:12:42,640 --> 00:12:44,240
Did you set the grind size too fine?

493
00:12:44,240 --> 00:12:45,040
Yes.

494
00:12:45,040 --> 00:12:46,040
It's too thin.

495
00:12:46,040 --> 00:12:46,760
Give it a try.

496
00:12:49,160 --> 00:12:50,760
(Showing off)
It's actually very easy.

497
00:12:50,760 --> 00:12:51,360
Commander.

498
00:12:52,520 --> 00:12:53,720
Is this yours?

499
00:12:53,720 --> 00:12:54,400
No.

500
00:12:54,400 --> 00:12:55,640
I just picked it up.

501
00:12:55,640 --> 00:12:57,160
I was looking for something to do.

502
00:13:02,920 --> 00:13:03,720
Can we eat this?

503
00:13:03,720 --> 00:13:04,000
Yes.

504
00:13:06,760 --> 00:13:07,600
You've never tried it?

505
00:13:08,640 --> 00:13:09,000
Try one.

506
00:13:09,000 --> 00:13:09,540
(Trusting his advice)

507
00:13:10,520 --> 00:13:11,160
Pretty bitter?

508
00:13:11,160 --> 00:13:12,540
(Then I'll give it a try)

509
00:13:12,920 --> 00:13:13,680
You can eat it.

510
00:13:14,220 --> 00:13:15,740
(Curious)

511
00:13:15,760 --> 00:13:16,680
It tastes like bitter coffee.

512
00:13:17,100 --> 00:13:18,300
(Not bad at all)

513
00:13:18,300 --> 00:13:20,100
(Starlight Cafe, Scene 1, Take 2)

514
00:13:22,380 --> 00:13:27,100
(Starlight Cafe)

515
00:13:41,880 --> 00:13:42,960
Welcome.

516
00:13:44,120 --> 00:13:47,160
Alright, everyone. Stop pretending.

517
00:13:47,160 --> 00:13:48,640
I know

518
00:13:48,920 --> 00:13:50,280
you've all been waiting for me.

519
00:13:51,140 --> 00:13:52,340
(Keyu approves)

520
00:13:52,780 --> 00:13:54,220
(Linghe's expression says it all)

521
00:13:54,620 --> 00:13:55,900
(Enjoying the show)

522
00:14:02,920 --> 00:14:03,520
This sofa...

523
00:14:03,520 --> 00:14:04,820
(Committed to the performance)

524
00:14:05,160 --> 00:14:07,800
With my three Gold Cards in hand,

525
00:14:07,800 --> 00:14:09,040
I'm not

526
00:14:09,040 --> 00:14:11,040
here for coffee today.

527
00:14:11,920 --> 00:14:12,920
You're kidding.

528
00:14:12,920 --> 00:14:13,800
I'm here to...

529
00:14:15,440 --> 00:14:15,920
Who is that?

530
00:14:15,920 --> 00:14:16,520
Get him out.

531
00:14:16,520 --> 00:14:18,160
Start with He Yiwei.

532
00:14:19,200 --> 00:14:20,980
(Instantly admits defeat)
Sorry.

533
00:14:21,920 --> 00:14:24,280
Now then, let me see whose coffee...

534
00:14:28,040 --> 00:14:29,640
I'll be ordering.

535
00:14:29,740 --> 00:14:31,420
(Who taught her to pause like that?)

536
00:14:33,760 --> 00:14:35,320
Let's see.

537
00:14:36,020 --> 00:14:38,900
(Starlight Cafe's signature
iced dad jokes)

538
00:14:38,900 --> 00:14:42,260
(Starlight Cafe)

539
00:14:42,480 --> 00:14:43,160
Which one of them...

540
00:14:44,240 --> 00:14:45,680
(The audience enjoying the spectacle)
is more entertaining than me?

541
00:14:45,680 --> 00:14:48,260
All of them.

542
00:14:48,260 --> 00:14:50,020
(Trying not to laugh)

543
00:14:50,220 --> 00:14:51,980
(Fails immediately)

544
00:14:52,040 --> 00:14:52,920
Have you forgotten

545
00:14:52,920 --> 00:14:54,520
my riddles?

546
00:14:54,520 --> 00:14:55,280
It's your favorite.

547
00:14:55,880 --> 00:14:56,680
Give us a couple.

548
00:14:56,680 --> 00:14:57,320
Let them hear it.

549
00:14:57,320 --> 00:14:59,360
(Let's hear everyone's verdict)
Come on, listen to this riddle.

550
00:14:59,360 --> 00:15:00,520
Let's see who can solve it.

551
00:15:01,040 --> 00:15:02,000
Let's hear it.

552
00:15:02,000 --> 00:15:02,400
Go ahead.

553
00:15:02,400 --> 00:15:03,000
I'm listening.

554
