00:29:29,380 --> 00:29:30,300
Lots of layers.

1098
00:29:30,300 --> 00:29:32,740
Start as an innocent sweetheart,
then go dark.

1099
00:29:32,740 --> 00:29:33,620
Oh.

1100
00:29:33,620 --> 00:29:34,380
Innocent-to-evil.

1101
00:29:34,380 --> 00:29:35,580
Evil-to-innocent works too.

1102
00:29:35,580 --> 00:29:37,020
I'll do evil-to-innocent-to-evil.

1103
00:29:37,020 --> 00:29:38,860
Watch me. It'll be super layered.

1104
00:29:38,860 --> 00:29:40,220
I've already planned it. Let's go.

1105
00:29:46,440 --> 00:29:48,000
Show me the monitor after the cut.

1106
00:29:48,200 --> 00:29:49,200
(Strictly checking the layers)
I'll review it.

1107
00:29:50,560 --> 00:29:51,440
Check the shot.

1108
00:29:51,640 --> 00:29:52,480
Review it, huh?

1109
00:29:53,500 --> 00:29:54,380
(Director Jin is online)

1110
00:29:54,480 --> 00:29:54,760
Okay.

1111
00:29:54,760 --> 00:29:55,840
Then, dear detectives...

1112
00:29:56,160 --> 00:29:56,960
Okay.

1113
00:29:56,960 --> 00:29:58,480
(Right in the heart)
I love it when you call me that.

1114
00:29:58,800 --> 00:29:59,680
(Switching to pro mode)
Time to work.

1115
00:30:00,360 --> 00:30:00,720
(Immediately obeys)
Okay.

1116
00:30:00,720 --> 00:30:01,040
Okay.

1117
00:30:01,600 --> 00:30:03,000
I'll help you get

1118
00:30:03,000 --> 00:30:04,360
the prep work done first.

1119
00:30:04,600 --> 00:30:05,200
Sure.

1120
00:30:05,960 --> 00:30:06,880
Should I wipe it off for you?

1121
00:30:06,880 --> 00:30:07,480
Wipe it off.

1122
00:30:07,480 --> 00:30:08,560
Don't wipe it.

1123
00:30:08,560 --> 00:30:09,320
No need?

1124
00:30:09,320 --> 00:30:09,880
Why wipe it?

1125
00:30:10,000 --> 00:30:11,360
(Let the noble detective decide)
Let me see if we should.

1126
00:30:11,480 --> 00:30:13,200
This seems like a fixed mark.

1127
00:30:13,200 --> 00:30:14,040
(Well-behaved)
That "God" thing,

1128
00:30:14,040 --> 00:30:14,800
can this be moved?

1129
00:30:15,200 --> 00:30:16,040
"God"?

1130
00:30:16,400 --> 00:30:17,480
You're being so flattering right now,

1131
00:30:17,480 --> 00:30:18,800
it's honestly a little heartbreaking.

1132
00:30:20,120 --> 00:30:20,840
There's no light here.

1133
00:30:20,840 --> 00:30:22,320
I don't stand where there's no light.

1134
00:30:22,320 --> 00:30:23,020
(Picky)

1135
00:30:23,120 --> 00:30:23,680
Then don't stand there.

1136
00:30:23,680 --> 00:30:24,400
No one's there.

1137
00:30:24,680 --> 00:30:25,120
Then don't stand there.

1138
00:30:25,120 --> 00:30:25,760
Come back.

1139
00:30:26,100 --> 00:30:27,620
(Watching the drama)

1140
00:30:27,620 --> 00:30:29,140
(Watching the drama +1)

1141
00:30:29,180 --> 00:30:31,300
(Gets in position fast)

1142
00:30:31,340 --> 00:30:34,300
(It's fine. The boat
already did a backflip)

1143
00:30:36,280 --> 00:30:37,200
(Relaxed after voting)
Once you wrap and come back,

1144
00:30:37,200 --> 00:30:38,440
it's the really scary kind.

1145
00:30:38,440 --> 00:30:39,760
You're not scared anymore, right, Ding?

1146
00:30:39,760 --> 00:30:40,520
How could I not be?

1147
00:30:40,520 --> 00:30:41,640
(Calling it out)
How could he not be?

1148
00:30:41,640 --> 00:30:42,120
Today he...

1149
00:30:43,600 --> 00:30:44,120
Where are you guys?

1150
00:30:44,120 --> 00:30:44,880
(Night vision mode)

1151
00:30:44,880 --> 00:30:46,080
You're the cheeky one.

1152
00:30:46,080 --> 00:30:48,320
Ning and I have done this
for so many years.

1153
00:30:48,320 --> 00:30:49,720
(Knows the routine)
We know the segments too well.

1154
00:30:49,720 --> 00:30:51,960
This season isn't as scary as before.

1155
00:30:51,960 --> 00:30:53,120
(Memory loading)
Back in Season 2,

1156
00:30:53,120 --> 00:30:53,920
it was really scary too.

1157
00:30:53,920 --> 00:30:55,440
The lights would go out for a second,

1158
00:30:55,440 --> 00:30:56,840
and then someone...

1159
00:30:56,840 --> 00:30:58,640
Plus, you were stuck in that spot.

1160
00:30:58,640 --> 00:30:59,600
You couldn't move.

1161
00:30:59,600 --> 00:31:01,600
(Night vision mode)
You could only watch him

1162
00:31:01,600 --> 00:31:02,400
get closer bit by bit.

1163
00:31:02,400 --> 00:31:03,400
Then he'd end up right in your face.

1164
00:31:04,120 --> 00:31:04,600
Like this.

1165
00:31:04,600 --> 00:31:05,160
(Imitating)

1166
00:31:05,160 --> 00:31:06,040
In Season 2,

1167
00:31:06,040 --> 00:31:07,400
that pilot episode was terrifying.

1168
00:31:07,400 --> 00:31:08,760
If Ding had recorded that pilot,

1169
00:31:08,760 --> 00:31:10,080
he'd have taken three hours.

1170
00:31:10,600 --> 00:31:11,280
Why?

1171
00:31:11,280 --> 00:31:13,320
You had to explore

1172
00:31:13,320 --> 00:31:15,640
a totally dark town
bell tower by yourself.

1173
00:31:15,640 --> 00:31:18,720
There were all kinds
of ghosts and traps inside.

1174
00:31:18,720 --> 00:31:20,080
(Sounds scary already)
I feel like I'd die in there.

1175
00:31:21,080 --> 00:31:22,200
Did you finish it?

1176
00:31:22,200 --> 00:31:23,280
(Very proud)
Every one of us finished it.

1177
00:31:23,680 --> 00:31:24,440
(Curious)
How long did it take?

1178
00:31:24,440 --> 00:31:26,400
I took about an hour.

1179
00:31:26,400 --> 00:31:27,400
(Impressed)
That's pretty fast.

1180
00:31:28,400 --> 00:31:29,160
(Not humble)
It was alright.

1181
00:31:29,160 --> 00:31:29,800
Who was the slowest?

1182
00:31:30,000 --> 00:31:31,480
Either He or Ning.

1183
00:31:31,480 --> 00:31:32,440
(Bold Bai)
Bai Yu was fast.

1184
00:31:32,440 --> 00:31:34,680
(Shocked)
Bai Yu got out in half an hour.

1185
00:31:34,680 --> 00:31:35,880
It was pretty scary.

1186
00:31:35,880 --> 00:31:38,480
I really think

1187
00:31:38,480 --> 00:31:39,680
someone super timid

1188
00:31:39,680 --> 00:31:40,560
wouldn't finish it.

1189
00:31:40,560 --> 00:31:41,520
Isn't that me?

1190
00:31:42,280 --> 00:31:43,120
Couldn't move an inch.

1191
00:31:43,120 --> 00:31:44,280
Seriously, not one step.

1192
00:31:44,280 --> 00:31:45,200
Now it's much better.

1193
00:31:45,200 --> 00:31:46,720
(Don't worry)
Now it's all brain teasers.

1194
00:31:47,200 --> 00:31:49,000
(Obsessed with the ultimate clue)
Where did the key clue go this time?

1195
00:31:49,520 --> 00:31:50,240
We'll hear it later.

1196
00:31:50,240 --> 00:31:51,360
Let's hear what it says later.

1197
00:31:51,640 --> 00:31:53,200
If you can't even narrow down
the culprit at the end,

1198
00:31:53,200 --> 00:31:54,200
you definitely won't think

1199
00:31:54,200 --> 00:31:55,440
to check that person's stuff.

1200
00:31:57,160 --> 00:31:58,240
(All from experience)
Unless, during the final discussion,

1201
00:31:58,240 --> 00:31:59,200
you can lock onto someone,

1202
00:31:59,200 --> 00:32:01,000
then you go through
their evidence again,

1203
00:32:01,000 --> 00:32:02,040
and you might find something.

1204
00:32:02,300 --> 00:32:03,540
(What are they doing?)

1205
00:32:03,540 --> 00:32:10,140
(Origami showdown)

1206
00:32:10,140 --> 00:32:10,900
(First one done)

1207
00:32:12,220 --> 00:32:12,980
(Start over)

1208
00:32:16,660 --> 00:32:17,540
(Success)

1209
00:32:17,820 --> 00:32:20,780
(Ning Bubble appears)

1210
00:32:20,920 --> 00:32:22,240
(Testing)
Ke, you're the detective tomorrow.

1211
00:32:23,480 --> 00:32:24,040
Seriously?

1212
00:32:24,040 --> 00:32:24,730
(+1 Shocked)
Seriously?

1213
00:32:25,640 --> 00:32:26,040
Yep.

1214
00:32:27,160 --> 00:32:28,080
How'd you know?

1215
00:32:28,080 --> 00:32:28,920
(Confused)
I don't know.

1216
00:32:28,920 --> 00:32:29,640
You're the killer,

1217
00:32:29,640 --> 00:32:31,240
